r to choose a different path. Their personal Pathways Coach, other professionals and a loved one who becomes their Support Agent, will assist them through every step of the way. Those close to the addicted individual are also trained to become genuine support and change agents in the individuals&#8217; life.<br \/>Through Pathways, addicted individuals and their loved ones create a source of light, strength, confidence, and peace. This is the key to true, lasting recovery from drugs and alcohol.<\/p>\n<h3>Court Reporting:<\/h3>\n<p>Pathways Real Life Recovery professionals are experienced with the legal process and all associated requirements. Pathways provides all necessary legal documents, such as progress reports, status updates, incident reporting and the like.<br \/>If a client violates court orders or probation requirements, Pathways understands that it is in the best interest of the client to report said violation through the appropriate channels.<\/p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify\">The Joint Commission Accreditation of Pathways Real Life Recovery in Sandy Utah<\/h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Pathways Real Life Recovery in Sandy Utah is honored to be a Joint Commission Accredited health care services provider. <a title=\"Facts About Joint Commission\" href=\"https:\/\/www.jointcommission.org\/about-us\/facts-about-the-joint-commission\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Joint Commission<\/a> is the United States&rsquo; oldest and largest institution for the establishment and management of quality and patient care safety standards in the national health care industry. The Joint Commission&rsquo;s panel consists of over 20 Commissioners, including physicians, administrators, educators, quality experts, and consumer advocates. The Commission accredits and certifies more than 22,000 hospitals, surgery centers, nursing homes, laboratories, and other health care organizations throughout the country.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">To earn <a title=\"Joint Commission Accreditation &amp; Certification\" href=\"https:\/\/www.jointcommission.org\/accreditation-and-certification\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accreditation by The Joint Commission<\/a>, a health care organization must undergo an intensive on-site examination by a Joint Commission survey team (from the Commission&rsquo;s 1,000 surveyors), a minimum of once every 3 years. Accreditation demonstrates the Commission&rsquo;s recognition of a health care organization&rsquo;s commitment to pursuit of the highest possible quality of care.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Joint Commission Accreditation measures a health care organization&rsquo;s performance level based on the Commission&rsquo;s established standards for quality and safety in patient care, treatment, and services. The Accreditation is essential to attracting the most highly qualified health care professionals, who want to work only for an accredited organization.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Accreditation can be required for obtaining Medicare certification without separate government inspection, by providers for whom it is applicable. It can also be a prerequisite for a provider&rsquo;s participation in managed care plans and may be a legal requirement for health care providers in some states.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">As an accredited health care provider, Pathways rehab center in Utah has access to The Joint Commission&rsquo;s tools for ongoing self-measurement of organizational performance. Further, <a title=\"Meet Our Team of Experts at Pathways- Get Professional Treatment With Master Level Therapists\" href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/our-team\/\">Pathways addiction recovery professionals<\/a> have access to the Commission&rsquo;s programs and initiatives for development of advanced skills and customized solutions to challenging problems in health care.<\/p>\n<h4>Get a Free Assessment from Pathways Real Life Recovery<\/h4>\n<p>For more